Xmppsh, a tiny shell via xmpp. Different from ssh, we can reach our 
bash using every kind of IM, or even behind the firewall.

Build:

    `make xmppsh`

Dependence:
    Mac:    require Xcode
    Linux:  require libxml2 openssl



Usage: xmppsh <MasterID> <Robot ID> <Password>
    MasterID: The main@jabber.org use to send out the cmd
    Robot ID: The bash@jabber.org use to receive the cmd
    Password: The bash@jabber.org Password

Gtalk is supported

Cmd:
    exit:   quit the entire program

